Pages 130 through 138 in the annotated slide deck show how JEPP can help host Scala from within a Python program.

I used jep 3.1: https://github.com/mrj0/jep


To compile ScalaUtils.scala:

scalac ScalaUtils.scala


To package the classes generated by the above compilation step into scala_utils.jar:

jar -cf scala_utils.jar scalython/*.class


To run the age_group.py script:

java -classpath /path/to/jep/build/java/jep.jar:/path/to/scala-library.jar:scala_utils.jar jep.Run age_group.py


